A remonstrance from the Lords and Commons assembled in Parliament at Dublin, concerning the estate of Ireland. The barbarousnesse of the bloody rebels, and a protestation of their complyance with the power of England, for reducing of that kingdome. This remonstrance is appointed to be printed and publishe[d] according to the directions of an order of Parliament. Ireland. Parliament.
[8] p.
Printed by William Bladen, printer to the Kings most Excellent maiesty, Dublin : anno Dom. 1646.
In the title, the "d" in "published" has failed to print. Signatures: A⁴. Annotation on Thomason copy: "March 27 1647". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
